Poland to Halt 1,236 Megawatts of Capacity This Weekend

-- B y   M a r e k   S t r z e l e c k i
-- 
2011-03-03T14:59:18Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-03/poland-to-halt-1-236-megawatts-of-capacity-this-weekend-1-.html
Power companies will halt 1,236
megawatts of electric capacity in  Poland  during the weekend,
according to data from grid operator  PSE Operator SA .  PGE SA will stop a 370-megawatt unit at  Elektrownia
Belchatow  at 10:01 p.m. tomorrow for 18 hours. A 206-megawatt
unit at Elektrownia Turow will be halted at 12:01 a.m. on March
5 for 48 hours. A 205-megawatt unit at PGEâ€™s Zespol Elektrowni
Dolna Odra will be shut at 12:01 a.m. on March 5 and restarted
on March 28, the data showed.  Electricite de  France  plans to shut a 225-megawatt
generator at Elektrownia Rybnik for 24 hours at 12:01 a.m. on
March 5, the data show. On the same day,  Tauron Polska Energia
SA (TPE)  will halt a 230-megawatt unit at  Elektrownia Laziska  for 36
hours from 6:01 a.m.  To contact the reporter on this story:
